  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Bhutan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Community-Based Natural Resource Management: Sustainable Livelihoods Program for Wamrong and Kangpara is continuation to the earlier project with RSPN. Wamrong and Kangpara are very remote districts in Eastern Bhutan where the need for environmental education is very high, combining this also with the general community development and sustainable livelihoods of the people living in these areas. The other component of the grant is a book (first ever of its kind) highlighting the history of environmental conservation (hence &quot;The Natural Heritage&quot;) during the 100 years of the current monarchy.</narrative>
  </description>
